     <font class="TallRed">How things should be done.<a name="109485579825035286">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          You know, I feel like this presidential election in November is tearing people apart faster than a Cable connection to the internet. I have never in my lifetime seen people so on edge about such a topic. Why? Well, its simple, its not about being 'democratic' or 'republican'...oh no...its a much bigger picture that people don't want to see.<br /><br />This is about ideologies. See, you're either on one side or you're on the other and here are the two sides: Science and Faith. They are both fine I guess, and usually can live in harmony, but the problem with the presidential election is that the reason that people are voting for one candidate or another is a moral decision. These morals are based on very structured ideologies that have existed for thousands of years. What is happening here is that on both sides people are screaming back and forth because the other side (naturally) challenges their ideology, or to be so frank, purpose in life. You can't tell someone to their face that God doesn't exist. You can't walk up to someone and tell them that their religion is a joke. You can't just walk up to somebody, take off their turban, and start stomping it. Not here. Not in America.<br /><br />On the other hand, no matter how much you know about faith and how many prophecies have shown validity over the thousands of years, you can't walk up to someone and tell them that "gravity doesn't exist, it is God holding each and everyone of us down to Earth". That's clearly not scientific. While I can't prove to you that it ISN'T God holding me down to the Earth, I cannot and will not attempt to understand your logic of thought.<br /><br />So, we have two sides: Science and Faith. Both sides are very powerful and have a very large base (and there are some anomalies in the middle, but let's keep this simple). Now, I see that people <span style="font-style:italic;">say</span> they don't want to talk about it-- try to dodge the subject and yet they really DO want to talk about it. Well...this Presidential Election has caused enough trouble and now I am going to offer a solution-- and as a true democracy we should be able to vote this in and put into effect. Ok, brace yourself.<br /><br />Instead of having a National {$Party_Name} Convention they should be training. Get on a treadmill everyday, learn how to box, Kung-Fu, or whathaveyou. Then, in November when we would normally be voting, we sit at home in front of our TVs which shows a circular dirt road (kind of like a loop). Then the gun goes off and the two presidential candidates ride off on chariots and race around the loop. Whoever wins the race first (or remains alive) is appointed president.<center><img src="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/blog/benhur.jpg" /></center>So there we have it people, thats my solution. Start writing promo letters to your Senator........now.<br />
