untered with this.... "well all the pictures I've ever seen".... I am so happy at times that in her being my step mother, I share no genetic material... LOL<br /><br />Now, on the other hand, you have the pure evolutionists who say science disproves God... Hmm.. how is this? "Well you see, we have the Big Bang".....Wait! It is God....BANG! That is the funny part, a scientist con no more disprove God, than they can prove God's existence. Personally, I bleieve Adam & Eve were cavemen, and we are their evolutionary children.<br /><br />I fully believe in science, and I fully believe in God. I fully believe in creationism, and I fully believe in evoulution. Why is it that people think the two do not exist together? One reason is the myth that we evolved from lower primates. I think that is garbage! Now on the surface J, you are thinking "see, that is the point" It isn't though. I do not doubt that ALL creatures have evolved on this planet. I can see evolution all around me. One of the easiest indicators is the structure of the human body, specifically height. 6 feet is the norm for a man now, where it was 4-5 feet, thousands of years ago. George Washington, and his 6 foot stature was a giant of a man, and that was merely 200 years ago. This is one of many indications you and I can see in a tengible form right before us. The irony is, it is the whole chimp to human theory that freaks out the non believers of evolution. Well we have found now that CroMag and Homo-Erectus primates evolved parallell to each other, not from each other, there is also very strong evidence now, that as the Homo-erectus man moved southward into France, Spain, and Italy, that more than likely they cross bred with the Cro-Magnon man, absorbing them into what we are now, as opposed to the old theory that Homo-Erectus killed them off. It is this logic that is bringing MANY in the science and anthropology community to believe now that we have evolved alongside chimps, and not from them. The question 